reviews.text:
Local chain of congee shops offering quick, cheap eats.  This branch has been renovated, and is brighter and more appealing than it's former self.
Boiling soup with choices of toppings is decent filling meal.
Loved the pomfret and meat cake (?). Both are very appetising
Carrot cake is good. Congee so so. Cheong fun is bad.
A small shop mainly selling congee.  Food quality was good and waitress were very active in serving.  Seats were very congested.  Ants were found on the table under the covering glass.
Local congee, fry dough shop. Good $, taste good.
